<h2 id="readintro">Readability Tests</h2>
<p>
Gunning Fog, Flesch Reading Ease,  and Flesch-Kincaid are <a href="#explanation">reading level algorithms</a> that can be helpful in determining how readable your content is. Reading level algorithms only provide a rough guide, as they tend to reward short sentences made up of short words. Whilst they're rough guides, they can give a useful indication as to whether you've pitched your content at the right level for your intended audience. 
</p>
<p class="skiplink">
[<a href="#toc">Back to the contents</a>]
</p>

